### LTI 1.3 manual test requests
###
### For VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP Client.
### Variables can be edited inline or set in a .env / http-client.env.json.
###
### These are manual exploratory checks — for the automated smoke run use:
###   ./scripts/test-lti.sh
###
### For end-to-end LMS testing, see docs/LTI-TESTING.md.

@base = https://jtwygbeceundfgnkirof.supabase.co
@fn   = {{base}}/functions/v1

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. JWKS — public, must return at least one RSA key
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{fn}}/lti-jwks
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Health probe — public, monitors keys + JWKS + DB
### Expect 200 + status=ok in normal operation; 503 + status=degraded if any
### check fails.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{fn}}/lti-health
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. OIDC init — happy-ish path
### This will 302 to the LMS auth_login_url IF a matching lti_platforms row
### exists for (issuer, client_id). With placeholder values it should 4xx.
### Edit @iss / @client_id below to test against a real registered platform.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@iss        = https://your-college.example.org
@client_id  = REPLACE_ME
@deployment = REPLACE_ME

GET {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init?iss={{iss}}&login_hint=test-user&target_link_uri={{fn}}/lti-launch&lti_deployment_id={{deployment}}&client_id={{client_id}}
Accept: text/html, application/json

### Same as above but POST form-encoded (Moodle uses POST)
POST {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

iss={{iss}}&login_hint=test-user&target_link_uri={{fn}}/lti-launch&lti_deployment_id={{deployment}}&client_id={{client_id}}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. OIDC init — negative cases (should all 4xx)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init
Accept: application/json

###
GET {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init?iss=https://example.invalid&login_hint=x&target_link_uri={{fn}}/lti-launch&lti_deployment_id=z
Accept: application/json

###
DELETE {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Launch — negative cases (should all 4xx, never 5xx)
### A real launch can only be done by an LMS that holds a private key matching
### one of its published JWKS keys. Use the IMS LTI Reference Tool or a
### Moodle/Canvas sandbox to drive a real launch end-to-end.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{fn}}/lti-launch

###
POST {{fn}}/lti-launch
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

id_token=not-a-jwt&state=not-a-state

### Tampered JWT (right shape, wrong signature)
POST {{fn}}/lti-launch
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

id_token=eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ0ZXN0In0.bogus_signature&state=anything

### GET on launch (it's POST-only per LTI spec)
GET {{fn}}/lti-launch

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Verify-platform — admin-only, requires Supabase JWT + matching college_id
###
### How to get a JWT:
###   - Log in to elec-mate.com as a user whose profiles.college_id matches
###     the platform's college_id (must be a college admin/staff).
###   - In browser devtools: localStorage.getItem('sb-jtwygbeceundfgnkirof-auth-token')
###     -> parse as JSON and copy `access_token`.
###
### Replace @jwt and @platform_id below.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@jwt = REPLACE_WITH_SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN
@platform_id = REPLACE_WITH_LTI_PLATFORMS_UUID

POST {{fn}}/lti-verify-platform
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "platform_id": "{{platform_id}}"
}

### Negative: missing auth header
POST {{fn}}/lti-verify-platform
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "platform_id": "{{platform_id}}"
}

### Negative: missing platform_id
POST {{fn}}/lti-verify-platform
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 7. Dynamic registration
### LMS hits this with ?openid_configuration=...&registration_token=...
### so opening it bare will 4xx. To test, configure your LMS's "Dynamic
### Registration URL" as:
###   {{fn}}/lti-dynamic-register?college_id=<uuid>
### and walk through the LMS admin flow.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{fn}}/lti-dynamic-register
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 8. CORS preflight sanity
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPTIONS {{fn}}/lti-jwks
Origin: https://example.com
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET

###
OPTIONS {{fn}}/lti-health
Origin: https://example.com
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET

###
OPTIONS {{fn}}/lti-oidc-init
Origin: https://example.com
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST

###
OPTIONS {{fn}}/lti-launch
Origin: https://example.com
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
